Why do you change this from array to vector?
I cant seem to find a way to have a map of enums to std::array if the arrays are not consistent

Ed has a comment that these are not needed, we just need to specify the first one.

```
   tagAccelerationFunction = 0,
```

Could you please address some of the comments in the previous commit?

Some outstanding ones that I remember: binary size, daemon start up time before and after this commit

Several questions here,

How do we maintain this list? What if a newly added resource missed modifying this list? A good default behavior is that we deny the access if the resource is not in the list. Is this implemented?

Also, how can we make sure this list is correct? I assume it is hand-written, right?

It is handwritten, the plan is to deny any patches to that entry in the privilege registry if a newly added resource missed adding to that list. Making sure that the list is correct could be a script/test that tries to patch every resource. If it fails any one, then the list isnt correct.
